{
  "title": "Patient · ethnicity (US Core / OMB)",
  "notes": "Ethnicity branch of the Patient__person edge (mapspec/etl/Patient__person.sql, view mapspec/views/Patient__person.view.json). One FHIR Patient → exactly one OMOP `person` row; this file varies ONLY the ethnicity input dimension. Race (US Core OMB 2106-3 White → race_concept_id 8527), gender (us-core-birthsex 'M' → 8507 MALE), and birthDate (2004-06-03) are held CONSTANT across every variant so the ethnicity diff is crisp.\n\nETL ethnicity logic (lines 64-68, 96-98 of Patient__person.sql):\n  ethnicity_concept_id        = COALESCE(NULLIF(omop_ethnicity_code,'')::int, e.concept_id, 0)\n  ethnicity_source_value      = COALESCE(omop_ethnicity_display, ethnicity_text)\n  ethnicity_source_concept_id = COALESCE(e.source_concept_id, 0)\nwhere e = LEFT JOIN cm.ethnicity_omb_to_omop ON source_code = ethnicity_omb_code.\n\nResolution PRIORITY: (1) omop-ethnicity extension (valueCoding.code = Athena concept_id as string, copied verbatim) wins; (2) else US Core us-core-ethnicity ombCategory code resolved via cm.ethnicity_omb_to_omop; (3) else 0.\n\nVerified live in vocab.concept (v20260227 bundle):\n  38003563 'Hispanic or Latino'     — domain Ethnicity, standard S, concept_code 'Hispanic'\n  38003564 'Not Hispanic or Latino' — domain Ethnicity, standard S, concept_code 'Not Hispanic'\n  8527 'White' (Race, S), 8507 'MALE' (Gender, S) — the held-constant race/gender concepts.\n\nethnicity_source_concept_id is ALWAYS 0 by design: cm.ethnicity_omb_to_omop carries source_concept_id=0 for both rows (the OMB ethnicity codes 2135-2/2186-5 are not loaded as concept_code under any non-standard Ethnicity vocabulary in Athena), so COALESCE(e.source_concept_id, 0) = 0. Per OMOP CDM v5.4 user_guidance this column 'tends to be zero'. See CLAUDE.md 'OMOP *_source_concept_id semantics — zero is fine'.\n\nThe person row is FULLY asserted (every non-null column listed; omitted columns asserted NULL). person_id-as-PK is omitted (surrogate, derived). location_id is NULL in every variant because these minimal Patients carry no address (no address element → forEachOrNull emits a null location row → stringToId(concat_ws('|', NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL)) — concat_ws skips NULLs yielding '' → but with all-NULL the key is empty; held NULL here for clarity as no address is present). provider_id / care_site_id are NULL (no generalPractitioner / managingOrganization).\n\nGrounding: variants 1 (Hispanic) and 2 (Not Hispanic) mirror the real cdm_ours_fhir.person output (8 Hispanic + 97 Not-Hispanic patients in the 100-patient Synthea cohort; ethnicity_source_value carries the human text, source_concept_id=0). Variant 3 (no ethnicity extension) and variant 4 (omop-ethnicity priority override) are hand-constructed minimal Patients whose expected rows are DERIVED from the ETL COALESCE chain.",
  "cases": [
